{"title":"AMBOSS Transfusión-2025-1","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Hematología/AMBOSS Transfusión-2025-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"AMBOSS\\NTransfusión ","guid":"ZUj0ZUsSe5bhD5XYVvYPeQ","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"## Resumen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"- Transfusión de sangre completa o componentes fraccionados para manejar numerosas condiciones","guid":"lyOESn1QgpNWowVLaEhnoA","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"- Células rojas empaquetadas (pRBCs): producto más transfundido para tratamiento de pérdida de sangre","guid":"xnTCWWP0PJxxd4l9NIqPDw","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"- La transfusión eleva niveles de hemoglobina (Hb) y mantiene perfusión orgánica y oxigenación tisular","guid":"zgMRQrvFT1bsB31akV1haQ","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"- Decisión basada en nivel de Hb, estado hemodinámico y comorbilidades","guid":"LJ7XBMTspLcJIwxrOmn1Wg","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"- Pruebas pretransfusionales obligatorias para minimizar riesgos de incompatibilidad","guid":"PgQuN_877nFybO0XWwD8Sg","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"## Sistemas de\\Ngrupos sanguíneos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"### Sistema\\NABO","guid":"EO-mtTyIqosw0Xqy0wyRLg","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"- Dos antígenos (A y B) presentes aislados, combinados o ausentes","guid":"vS51z-jzTx-pJ4XNDSXvxw","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"8","text":"- Anticuerpos anti-A y/o anti-B se forman espontáneamente en individuos antígeno-negativos","guid":"CYIhJHzXF1AlkBzPbsRwFw","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"8","text":"- Pueden desencadenar reacciones hemolíticas agudas","guid":"Ubk4T6v8s-h2jYHunFgdsg","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"8","text":"- Tipos\\Nsanguíneos\\NABO:","guid":"D8bGqf6RwR3PoRwgCd_06g","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"- Tipo O","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"- Prevalencia: ~45%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"- Antígenos: Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"13","text":"- Anticuerpos: Anti-A y anti-B","guid":"0jJvntpp3igWeC_EvL9xww","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"13","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: O","guid":"k2tjmRCZlgLtGzlMJsFZBg","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"13","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: O, A, B, AB (donante universal)","guid":"W-40iwr_1oBN0ODo26F7xg","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"13","text":"- Puede recibir FFP de: O, A, B, AB (receptor universal FFP)","guid":"cYUdctyVUi00DttKSsSJAw","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"13","text":"- Puede donar FFP a: O","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"21","parent":"12","text":"- Tipo A","guid":"","children":[{"id":"22","parent":"21","text":"- Prevalencia: ~40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"21","text":"- Antígenos: A","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"21","text":"- Anticuerpos: Anti-B","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"21","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: A, O","guid":"YS_KEq9n0bin9cmo65zlTg","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"21","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: A, AB","guid":"inWuDtlyuQZQdDimkxS9Qw","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"21","text":"- Puede recibir FFP de: A, AB","guid":"80jyHnlix9ZxrHaMQpSrCQ","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"21","text":"- Puede donar FFP a: A, O","guid":"idIsHVN4fta292z01R6N0Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"29","parent":"12","text":"- Tipo B","guid":"","children":[{"id":"30","parent":"29","text":"- Prevalencia: ~10%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"31","parent":"29","text":"- Antígenos: B","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"29","text":"- Anticuerpos: Anti-A","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"29","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: B, O","guid":"EodjAgcXZ5b9P0RPvUcKfg","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"29","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: B, AB","guid":"K9ew2SnL2jm5zylpCSlq1A","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"29","text":"- Puede recibir FFP de: B, AB","guid":"563hY9ItRZUYq3Rgwg65VQ","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"29","text":"- Puede donar FFP a: B, O","guid":"O6RubP0caVBrS0AQNWWSrw","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"12","text":"- Tipo AB","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"- Prevalencia: ~5%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"- Antígenos: A y B","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"- Anticuerpos: Ninguno","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: AB, A, B, O (receptor universal)","guid":"jQyehTiHcGjdT2BRA_2ffw","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"37","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: AB","guid":"IlDIp_Cs-WxukTJx1DL42g","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"37","text":"- Puede recibir FFP de: AB","guid":"rCHyai6P7wHf30lRyBN7aQ","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"37","text":"- Puede donar FFP a: AB, A, B, O (donante universal FFP)","guid":"fbNlFEE1Yi0pl_EVpSdIkg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"45","parent":"7","text":"### Sistema\\NRhesus","guid":"M7bpU8JZsp9lgwTTRBkH7g","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"- >45 antígenos Rhesus (Rh), siendo Rh(D) el más inmunogénico y significativo","guid":"mJvNyBHHrB9PLsWU1SP03g","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"- Anticuerpos anti-Rh generalmente se forman tras exposición a RBCs Rh-positivos","guid":"gdBKEXsi0HIWDIxMJ5uS4g","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"- Pueden causar enfermedad hemolítica del feto/recién nacido y reacciones transfusionales","guid":"KePWl7T6QKYoUezl5bMRAw","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"45","text":"- Tipos Rhesus:","guid":"juQtgA22uwEvFfaIkF7Qng","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"- Rh-negativo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"- Prevalencia: 1-15%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"- Antígeno Rh(D): Ausente","guid":"glkm4PlZBchw8VEvuNyTDw","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"- Anticuerpos: Pueden formarse tras sensibilización","guid":"YP4R_W4ucEf_e-BYb-Hutw","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"50","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: Rh-negativo (preferentemente)","guid":"EfMSk1e_6Q_wD7QDkXlLgQ","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"50","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: Rh-negativo, Rh-positivo","guid":"B33CT-SYXTeZ7tK88ZiJXA","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"49","text":"- Rh-positivo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"- Prevalencia: 85-99%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"- Antígeno Rh(D): Presente","guid":"y3Chk-virwlt0d0g52XQHA","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"- Anticuerpos: No anticuerpos anti-Rh","guid":"hoDN1T5u9Gab71T8cdpPow","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"- Puede recibir RBCs de: Rh-positivo, Rh-negativo","guid":"z0ZF7fs1QPZs4iTbOJurLA","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"56","text":"- Puede donar RBCs a: Rh-positivo","guid":"VLpBnSp30ZJL88Gqr4Cu3A","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"7","text":"### Sistemas extendidos\\Nde antígenos RBC","guid":"OzkuUMyVIXFMPPfS8DJ3Mg","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"- Antígenos adicionales pueden desencadenar formación de anticuerpos","guid":"Ks3e0Ta1Y8o46aFY7VcbZg","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"- Sistema Rhesus: Antígenos no-D (Rh(C), Rh(E))","guid":"aIpGcRI9nSoZFcvTLBon3A","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"- Sistema Kell: Incluye antígenos K (K1), k (K2), Kp(a), Kp(b), Js(a), Js(b)","guid":"7zf8L6vf4weaUATgl2CqvA","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"- Sistema Duffy: Seis receptores glucoproteicos en RBCs","guid":"tUhpGZrj_qkwgNbm_KFrBQ","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"62","text":"- Sistema Kidd: Tres antígenos RBC raros (Jka, Jkb, JK3)","guid":"90HfiFxmee0sK1p0rAPMHw","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"62","text":"- Sistema MNS: >40 antígenos RBC, menos significativos clínicamente","guid":"27nKb6k1A-PAXESvDeOboA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"69","parent":"0","text":"## Medidas de\\Nseguridad transfusional","guid":"L2FF6n7S3G6i_K8jwtfb-A","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"### Medidas del\\Nbanco de sangre","guid":"4uASotRjX5RmGKutTaeYVw","children":[{"id":"71","parent":"70","text":"- Productos pueden ser alogénicos (donante) o autólogos (propios)","guid":"TFe0YnY65xeM19o3eO-wWA","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"70","text":"- Control para donantes: cuestionario (DHQ), pruebas infecciosas, leucorreducción","guid":"WxDf1h508v86vn7GReQHLQ","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"70","text":"- Procesamiento adicional para grupos de alto riesgo","guid":"x6NSdV3XgQ-D-Nj5ynCTtg","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"70","text":"- Sangre autóloga: procesamiento mínimo intraoperatorio","guid":"qszAMVJwiEXLHGR6usVCjw","children":[]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"69","text":"### Control de\\Ninfecciones","guid":"4u-qAvwL4P1lM5hnhD_1hA","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"- Leucorreducción: filtración de leucocitos de productos sanguíneos celulares","guid":"kAHUhp8-vPM--fcrWkwPvQ","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"- Detección de infecciones\\Nen donaciones:","guid":"5g20iJz_k7GO88chy-zIGQ","children":[{"id":"78","parent":"77","text":"- Rutinaria en EE.UU.: HIV, hepatitis B/C, HTLV, West Nile, Zika, sífilis, Chagas","guid":"dIlToGzftLQIIeAmYtsYAA","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"77","text":"- Adicional en regiones endémicas: babesiosis, hepatitis A/E, malaria","guid":"bFoWHXMGlenHnPoqVUX5HQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"69","text":"### Procesamiento\\Nadicional","guid":"wpEu-JIRJDbaQlUzySz6BA","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"- Irradiación: inactiva linfocitos para reducir riesgo de GvHD asociada a transfusión","guid":"SN6DfL8NnoOAVSWdu8SP4Q","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"- Lavado: reemplaza plasma para reducir riesgo de reacción alérgica","guid":"xzcG5NOY46TUwjVldkSngw","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"- Reducción de volumen: previene sobrecarga circulatoria durante transfusión","guid":"08Kiv6iRcev5Jo26udFBUA","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"69","text":"### Prácticas de seguridad\\Npretransfusionales","guid":"QyFNJ9A6l7IPAu-w4v1roA","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"- Considerar transfusión cuando beneficios superan riesgos","guid":"ETjlf9de74cEPwrwUoH9Eg","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"84","text":"- Elegir umbrales específicos según condición y paciente","guid":"gkE9N0h4lt1KhAcpWHdBfg","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"84","text":"- Obtener consentimiento informado cuando sea posible","guid":"8mi40updSlcIPlCmSygB0Q","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"84","text":"- Completar pruebas pretransfusionales","guid":"HpQcXgRUVjLeH2Wn61DWqQ","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"84","text":"- Seguir requisitos de compatibilidad","guid":"ksgm6vyygpErtTx5BUtutQ","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"84","text":"- No retrasar transfusiones que salvan vidas","guid":"UtadXU7x6bF8TlyjHdtPkQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"91","parent":"69","text":"### Lista de verificación\\Npretransfusional","guid":"YYz9OApq5mEVzBsbH_tuhQ","children":[{"id":"92","parent":"91","text":"- Revisar registros para identificar requisitos especiales","guid":"NBrEpI2LugMMUrXMBvslsw","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"91","text":"- Discutir riesgos, beneficios y alternativas","guid":"dflZ8cQhalOZ2QI7hHB-Gg","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"91","text":"- Documentar consentimiento informado","guid":"_08LFtfJ60a0C3EU-ucR8Q","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"91","text":"- Solicitar pruebas pretransfusionales","guid":"CyhOEJxrMo4AUfeHWiB_5w","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"91","text":"- Transfundir dentro de horario normal laboral si no es urgente","guid":"VDwtoE-ScnwvjjswGL4NXg","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"91","text":"- Usar productos completamente cruzados cuando estén disponibles","guid":"GA3cR_qZNB7Qk4f6NEO22g","children":[]}]},{"id":"98","parent":"69","text":"### Solicitudes y\\Nprescripciones","guid":"Nx26v3NDziUbfExyyJFJOQ","children":[{"id":"99","parent":"98","text":"- Asegurar identificación correcta del paciente","guid":"etI5T3zagujXZaSUI5fibA","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"98","text":"- Documentar razones para transfusión","guid":"QtHtbPdkIArrVfQEXlLRsg","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"98","text":"- Especificar tipo y número de unidades","guid":"wGW8ix5x4khB6i4v-SveeA","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"98","text":"- Indicar velocidad o duración","guid":"7KRCMXJhqkKrYtsfPzPJWw","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"98","text":"- Señalar requisitos especiales","guid":"oyk78IVExiBnIVG9nlO2KA","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"98","text":"- Incluir datos del médico solicitante","guid":"wC-AnNQE9_3ZO5rCQS6lfw","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"69","text":"### Verificación de seguridad\\Nantes de administración","guid":"CRnAg-qPrA8JFqZ7yxVUtQ","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"- Confirmar identidad del paciente","guid":"k9nKeELLCpQDdVy4gpAW8A","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"- Verificar productos sanguíneos correctos","guid":"ahQnG78r7JIkZSPbhaPmQw","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"105","text":"- Asegurar que contenedores estén intactos","guid":"cEJ6kWIodIkEC_Hxp60IoQ","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"105","text":"- Comparar identificadores del paciente y producto","guid":"L3jeBPDGyqFrF1cH2okSWg","children":[]}]},{"id":"110","parent":"69","text":"### Administración\\Nde transfusión","guid":"2SWzT1G5qzJlA72R-TbDLg","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"- Equipamiento: set estándar de infusión, calentadores si es necesario","guid":"5c9MDiM3w8Oq-zMv--l1fQ","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"- Velocidad: más lenta primeros 15 minutos, completar en 4 horas","guid":"K0ahv4aY9OXkY5zGGLKclg","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"110","text":"- Precauciones: no administrar otros medicamentos por mismo tubo","guid":"uZ9MCIQrtwPg0plF0pVhnQ","children":[]},{"id":"114","parent":"110","text":"- No usar antipiréticos/antihistamínicos/esteroides rutinariamente","guid":"CNmVd0fIvaUBo1zzC1tREg","children":[]}]},{"id":"115","parent":"69","text":"### Monitorización","guid":"yWQmJCLWs74GISqI8_Za8Q","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"- Verificar estado clínico y signos vitales para cada unidad","guid":"3G1KLMHaisnhJNROkjeaWA","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"- Controlar antes, 15 minutos después, y 60 minutos tras completar","guid":"Kxya7f2UiFV9bqpS4RkVRg","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"- Vigilar sobrecarga de fluidos","guid":"GqWv1BDljxMZbcnePEDLJA","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"- Observar pacientes hospitalizados 24 horas post-transfusión","guid":"BdsqnuV5ckcVc9BT-QvZnQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"120","parent":"0","text":"## Pruebas\\Npretransfusionales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"121","parent":"120","text":"### Objetivo y\\Nmétodos","guid":"rX7kDqAg9ytxdpjtxv4Ftg","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"- Garantizar compatibilidad entre receptor y donante","guid":"zedFFnKnzWA9PqPkRUSwcg","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"121","text":"- Principalmente mediante hemaglutinación","guid":"b9AXk2ZCu0FpXQ-YANfEAg","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"121","text":"- Requisitos según\\Nproducto e institución:","guid":"yCY6z8wPZlipqzpUWRJhLw","children":[{"id":"125","parent":"124","text":"- RBC: Tipificación, cribado de anticuerpos y prueba cruzada","guid":"OWT8n3fxVInF93S3t7cOTQ","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"124","text":"- FFP: Tipificación sanguínea","guid":"llDoq0Yj1VLrtoeytNVg-A","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"124","text":"- Plaquetas/crioprecipitado: Tipificación puede ser necesaria","guid":"M_KtxpA-MRJN23ztV8D2qA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"120","text":"### Tiempos\\Nde respuesta","guid":"qqEIDTPJY7k78nQVv8vSPw","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"- Tipificación: hasta 25 minutos","guid":"xCnX2pSQPBQKxghr4lBgOw","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"- Tipo y cribado: hasta 75 minutos","guid":"0E_q9U53UPC_ggzAXUcfYQ","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"128","text":"- Tipo, cribado y cruce: hasta 120 minutos","guid":"OjWk1ilUNhLN9zfl-tkYQw","children":[]}]},{"id":"132","parent":"120","text":"### Pruebas\\Nrutinarias","guid":"Xl2svzraTEy9d0ujBEJe9A","children":[{"id":"133","parent":"132","text":"- Alta probabilidad durante admisión: tipo y cribado al llegar","guid":"PZiEEWAlBzGLEyGnXQ-_Lg","children":[]},{"id":"134","parent":"132","text":"- Alta probabilidad en próximas horas: tipo, cribado y cruce inmediato","guid":"i7E3rhmHTg9K6lcxOM3ddA","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"132","text":"- Fenotipo RBC extendido: para pacientes con necesidades transfusionales a largo plazo","guid":"relXbQO9ayVDLo_Taoar9A","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"120","text":"### Descripción de pruebas\\Npretransfusionales","guid":"ndKTICAY1q4phUUj9i5DxQ","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"- Tipo y\\Ncribado:","guid":"vbhsd2_HHGQJxnlwSv89YQ","children":[{"id":"138","parent":"137","text":"- Tipificación sanguínea: determina grupo ABO y Rh mediante tipificación directa e inversa","guid":"V1AFXhKXwqX6bMYIJ_hgWg","children":[]},{"id":"139","parent":"137","text":"- Cribado de anticuerpos RBC: detecta aloanticuerpos inesperados","guid":"TO3VFzGpFgOCoRMbxw9Rtw","children":[]}]},{"id":"140","parent":"136","text":"- Prueba\\Ncruzada:","guid":"rKcMEu8cT1VwP5Fe8SJcdA","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"- Electrónica: selección por sistema informático (~5 minutos)","guid":"fcELh6clFLpz0WNb6oXFfQ","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"140","text":"- Serológica: mezcla muestras\\Nde donante y receptor","guid":"","children":[{"id":"143","parent":"142","text":"- Con cribado negativo: aglutinación directa (~10-45 minutos)","guid":"wRQykT9wB5kXUyqJjve6GA","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"142","text":"- Con cribado positivo: test de Coombs indirecto (>2 horas)","guid":"ilGCCtiLX6wLde0IQbLgYA","children":[]}]}]}]}]},{"id":"145","pa